Liberty Global PLC (NASDAQ:LBTYA) Lifted to "Buy" at BidaskClub


July 23, 2017 09:01·





Liberty Global
Liberty Global (NASDAQ:LBTYA) had its stock price target reduced to $41.00 by Pivotal Research Group in a report issued 7/18/2017. Following the completion of the transaction, the director now directly owns 761,816 shares in the company, valued at $16,577,116.16. Bronfman E.L. Rothschild L.P. now owns 4,460 shares of the company's stock valued at $103,000 after buying an additional 959 shares during the period.
In other Liberty Global PLC news, Director John C. Malone bought 242,778 shares of Liberty Global PLC stock in a transaction on Wednesday, July 12th. Finally, Quest Investment Management LLC purchased a new position in Liberty Global PLC during the first quarter worth about $13,731,000. KCG Holdings Inc. acquired a new position in Liberty Global PLC during the first quarter valued at about $253,000.Several research firms recently issued reports on LILA. The firm's 50 day moving average price is $30.86 and its 200-day moving average price is $33.57. The stock's market capitalization is 4.37B, it has a 52-week low of 19.10 and a 52-week high of 36.57. CA bought a new stake in shares of Liberty Global PLC during the first quarter worth about $201,000. If you are viewing this story on another domain, it was illegally stolen and republished in violation of United States and worldwide trademark & copyright law. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own 54.62% of the company's stock.

